            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Thanks for the report. It's a known issue, covered by existing issues.\r\n\r\nI believe external UIs could work around this, though. For example, look at the cursor in [oni](https://github.com/extr0py/oni): its rendering is completely unknown to nvim. @extr0py would \"externalizing\" the `'cursorline'` option make sense? E.g., it is sent as a UI event and nvim core does nothing with it. ",
