        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Externalizing the `cursorline` and `cursorcolumn` makes a lot of sense to me. As I understand it, it's really a rendering nicety that happens in screen space, which makes it very easy for the external UIs to handle (as opposed to something like syntax highlighting, which can potentially span across the buffer). \r\n\r\nFor oni (and likely the other front-ends), it would actually make rendering faster if we do cursorline/cursorcolumn via the external UI, and open the door for some extra UI-extensibility that wouldn't be possible with the existing strategy. Totally on board üëç üëç ",
